{
  "texts": [
    "Vnet CNN model is trained on 3D MRI scans to perform image segmentation [106].Left part of the architecture consists of the compression path and right part decompress the signal until its original size reached.• Left Side This side divided into different stages and every stage comprise one to three convolutional layers.",
    "Each stage residual function is learnt all layers connected and added to the last output convolutional layer of that stage in order to enable learning a residual function.Convolutional performed in each stage use volumetric kernels having size 5 × 5 × 5 voxels.",
    "(Voxels represent the value on s regular grid in 3d space).",
    "Output of the pooling layers needed for back propagation.",
    "Down sampling also perform because it helps to increase the respective field."
  ]
}